cking", "summary": "Shot blocking is how willing he is to get in a shooting lane \u2014 counted straight from the NHL's play-by-play. He's logged 75 blocked shots over his last 241 games (0.9 per 60 minutes on the ice), and the grade ranks that against other forwards.", "caveat": "Home-scorer count -- arena bias is real (some rinks record far more than others). Read big gaps as signal, small ones as noise."}, "takeaways60": {"receipts": [{"label": "Puck stripping rate", "value": "1.55 / 60", "tone": "neutral"}], "method": "Per-60 rate over 3 seasons (TOI-weighted), ranked vs same-position peers.", "label": "Puck stripping", "summary": "Puck stripping is how often he strips the puck off an opponent \u2014 counted straight from the NHL's play-by-play. He's logged 126 takeaways over his last 241 games (1.5 per 60 minutes on the ice), and the grade ranks that against other forwards.", "caveat": "Home-scorer count -- arena bias is real (some rinks record far more than others). Read big gaps as signal, small ones as noise."}, "giveaways60": {"receipts": [{"label": "Puck security rate", "value": "4.30 / 60", "tone": "neutral"}, {"label": "Direction", "value": "fewer is better", "tone": "neutral"}], "method": "Per-60 rate over 3 seasons (TOI-weighted), ranked vs same-position peers.", "label": "Puck security", "summary": "Puck security is how often he turns the puck over (fewer is better) \u2014 counted straight from the NHL's play-by-play. He's logged 350 giveaways over his last 241 games (4.3 per 60 minutes on the ice), and the grade ranks that against other forwards.", "caveat": "Home-scorer count -- arena bias is real (some rinks record far more than others). Read big gaps as signal, small ones as noise."}, "primary_assists60": {"receipts": [{"label": "Playmaking rate", "value": "1.73 / 60", "tone": "neutral"}], "method": "Per-60 rate over 3 seasons (TOI-weighted), ranked vs same-position peers.", "label": "Playmaking", "summary": "Playmaking is how often he makes the p